article.description: Jennifer Warkenthien scored 18 points to lead four Jackrabbits in double figures, and South Dakota State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24) defeated IPFW 71-48 Saturday to remain unbeaten in the Summit League.
article.headline: Four Jackrabbits reach double figures against Mastodons
article.linkText: Warkenthien paces No. 21 South Dakota St. win
article.story:
FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Jennifer Warkenthien scored 18 points to lead four Jackrabbits in double figures, and South Dakota State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24) defeated IPFW 71-48 Saturday to remain unbeaten in the Summit League.

Maria Boever had 12 points for South Dakota State (14-1, 3-0), which led 31-15 at halftime. Jill Young added 11 points and nine rebounds, and Ketty Cornemann had 10 points.

Warkenthien and Boever each grabbed seven rebounds as the Jackrabbits beat the Mastodons 38-32 on the boards. South Dakota State outscored IPFW 30-20 in the paint and had 15 points off turnovers.

The Jackrabbits shot 45 percent overall and 76 percent from the free-throw line. The Mastodons (2-11, 1-2) managed just 35 percent from the field and 62 percent on free throws.

Chelsey Jackson, with 18 points, was the only IPFW player in double figures.
